Italian Business Confidence Unexpectedly Rises in August

-- B y   A n d r e w   D a v i s
-- 
2011-08-30T09:00:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-30/italian-business-confidence-unexpectedly-rises-in-august.html
Italian business confidence
unexpectedly rose in August as manufacturers become more
optimistic about demand for their goods.  The manufacturing-sentiment index rose to 99.9 from a
revised 98.8 in July the national statistics institute said in
 Rome  today. Economists had predicted a reading of 97.1,
according to the median of 16 estimates in a Bloomberg News
survey  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Davis in Rome at 
